 Finally, Elvis maintains, we should consider greed: asteroids likely hold vast riches, such as large platinum deposits, and mining them could provide both a new industry and a funding source for bolder space exploration. Elvis explains how each motive can be satisfied, and how they help one another. From the origins of life, to “space billiards,” and space sports, Elvis looks at how asteroids may be used in the not-so-distant future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAsteroids. 0aNear-Earth objects. 0aSpace mining. 7aSCIENCE / Astronomy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2021 Englishz978311075416208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2021z9783110753936oZDB-23-DPC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073923740uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300258387?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300258387423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300258387/original  a978-3-11-073923-7  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075416-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DPCb2021